1. Arbitrage-Free Pricing Models
Project: No-Arbitrage Stock Portfolio Simulator
Goal: Build a Python-based simulator that models a one-period binomial market and tests for arbitrage opportunities.
Features:
Simulate different stock prices with given parameters (𝑆0,𝑢,𝑑,𝑟).
Implement a function to check if a portfolio satisfies no-arbitrage conditions.
Visualize results (e.g., portfolio value over time, arbitrage checks).
Tools: Python, NumPy, Matplotlib.
